Role:
This project will: 
-  expand access to telecommunications services, as well as improve the quality of service being offered; 
-  encourage competition leading to lower tariffs, and the introduction of new services; 
-  improve the basic infrastructure required to promote further private sector development; and
- promote additional investment and growth to other sectors in the Democratic Republic of Congo through the demonstration effect.
IFC's role in the project is firstly to support a current client and expansion of an existing project with funding that is not available elsewhere, and secondly, to finance the extension of the network to provide access to the people and businesses of the DRC, which currently have inadequate, or in some cases, no telecommunications service.  The DRC has been gradually emerging from a decade of political instability and conflict which have taken a heavy toll on the country and its 55 million people.

